Angola Detains Protesters Demanding President Quits, Radio Says

-- B y   C a n d i d o   M e n d e s
-- 
2011-03-07T08:37:35Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-07/angola-detains-protesters-demanding-president-quits-radio-says.html
Angolan security forces detained 20
protesters demanding the “departure” of President Jose Eduardo
dos Santos, who has been in power since 1979, Radio Ecclesia
reported, without citing anyone.  Detentions included three journalists of the independent
weekly Novo Jornal who were covering the demonstration in the
capital, Luanda, Radio Ecclesia said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Candido Mendes in Luanda,  Angola  at 
 cmendes6@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Antony Sguazzin in Johannesburg at 
 asguazzin@bloomberg.net . 